Laboratório 01 - Aprendizagem da Máquina - Regressão Linear¶

Este relatório descreve as atividades inerentes ao laboratório 01 da disciplina de aprendizagem da máquina ministrada pelo professor Leandro Marinho em 2018.2 na Universidade Federal de Campina Grande.¶

Todas as atividades descritas abaixo tomaram como ponto de partida o código fonte presente em github.com/llSourcell/linear_regression_live e descrito neste vídeo: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XdM6ER7zTLk.¶

As questões respondidas abaixo tem como tema Regressão Linear, tal como discutido em sala de aula.¶

Os dados correspondem à anos de escolaridade por salário anual ao final da formação para um conjunto de diferentes profissões.¶

1. Rode o mesmo programa nos dados contendo anos de escolaridade (primeira coluna) versus salário (segunda coluna). Baixe os dados no link: income.csv. Esse exemplo foi trabalhado em sala de aula.¶

Segue código exemplo testado com base no arquivo income.csv, conforme indicado.¶

import plotly.figure_factory as ff
from numpy import *
import pandas as pd
import plotly.graph_objs as go

# y = mx + b
# m is slope, b is y-intercept
def compute_error_for_line_given_points(b, m, points):
    totalError = 0
    for i in range(0, len(points)):
        x = points.x[i]
        y = points.y[i]
        totalError += (y - (m * x + b)) ** 2
    return totalError / float(len(points))

def step_gradient(b_current, m_current, points, learningRate):
    b_gradient = 0
    m_gradient = 0
    N = float(len(points))
    for i in range(0, len(points)):
        x = points[i, 0]
        y = points[i, 1]
        b_gradient += -(2/N) * (y - ((m_current * x) + b_current))
        m_gradient += -(2/N) * x * (y - ((m_current * x) + b_current))
    new_b = b_current - (learningRate * b_gradient)
    new_m = m_current - (learningRate * m_gradient)
    return [new_b, new_m]

def gradient_descent_runner(points, starting_b, starting_m, learning_rate, num_iterations, plot=0):
    b = starting_b
    m = starting_m
    error = 0
    rsss = pd.DataFrame(dict(iteration=[],RSS=[]))
    for i in range(num_iterations):
        b, m = step_gradient(b, m, array(points), learning_rate)
        error = compute_error_for_line_given_points(b, m, points)
    
    return [b, m]

def run():
    points = pd.read_csv("income.csv")
    
    learning_rate = 0.0001
    initial_b = 0 # initial y-intercept guess
    initial_m = 0 # initial slope guess
    num_iterations = 1000
    print("Starting gradient descent at b = {0}, m = {1}, error = {2}".format(initial_b, initial_m, compute_error_for_line_given_points(initial_b, initial_m, points)))
    print("Running...")
    #print(points.info())
    [b, m] = gradient_descent_runner(points, initial_b, initial_m, learning_rate, num_iterations, 1)
    print("After {0} iterations b = {1}, m = {2}, error = {3}".format(num_iterations, b, m, compute_error_for_line_given_points(b, m, points)))

    
if __name__ == '__main__':
    run()

Running...
After 1000 iterations b = -0.18234255376510086, m = 3.262182267596014, error = 103.39842291729683

from plotly import version
from plotly.offline import download_plotlyjs, init_notebook_mode, plot, iplot

#import plotly.offline as py
import plotly.figure_factory as ff
from numpy import *
import pandas as pd
import plotly.graph_objs as go

# y = mx + b
# m is slope, b is y-intercept
def compute_error_for_line_given_points(b, m, points):
    totalError = 0
    for i in range(0, len(points)):
        x = points.x[i]
        y = points.y[i]
        totalError += (y - (m * x + b)) ** 2
    return totalError / float(len(points))

def step_gradient(b_current, m_current, points, learningRate):
    b_gradient = 0
    m_gradient = 0
    N = float(len(points))
    for i in range(0, len(points)):
        x = points[i, 0]
        y = points[i, 1]
        b_gradient += -(2/N) * (y - ((m_current * x) + b_current))
        m_gradient += -(2/N) * x * (y - ((m_current * x) + b_current))
    new_b = b_current - (learningRate * b_gradient)
    new_m = m_current - (learningRate * m_gradient)
    return [new_b, new_m]

def gradient_descent_runner(points, starting_b, starting_m, learning_rate, num_iterations, plot=0):
    b = starting_b
    m = starting_m
    error = 0
    rsss = pd.DataFrame(dict(iteration=[],RSS=[]))
    for i in range(num_iterations):
        b, m = step_gradient(b, m, array(points), learning_rate)
        error = compute_error_for_line_given_points(b, m, points)
        #print("After {0} iterations b = {1}, m = {2}, error = {3}".format(i+1, b, m, error))
        rsss = rsss.append({'iteration': i+1,'RSS': error}, ignore_index=True)
    

    table = ff.create_table(rsss)
    iplot(table, filename='simple_table')
    
    return [b, m]

def run():
    points = pd.read_csv("income.csv")
    init_notebook_mode(connected=True)
    learning_rate = 0.0001
    initial_b = 0 # initial y-intercept guess
    initial_m = 0 # initial slope guess
    num_iterations = 1000
    print("Starting gradient descent at b = {0}, m = {1}, error = {2}".format(initial_b, initial_m, compute_error_for_line_given_points(initial_b, initial_m, points)))
    print("Running...")
    #print(points.info())
    [b, m] = gradient_descent_runner(points, initial_b, initial_m, learning_rate, num_iterations, 1)
    print("After {0} iterations b = {1}, m = {2}, error = {3}".format(num_iterations, b, m, compute_error_for_line_given_points(b, m, points)))

    
if __name__ == '__main__':
    run()

3. O que acontece com o RSS ao longo das iterações (aumenta ou diminui) se você usar 1000 iterações? Plote o RSS vs número de iterações.¶

Novamente temos exatamento o mesmo código da questão acima, exceto por plotar o RSS em um gráfico bidimencional a cada iteração ao invés de apenas anumerar os valores em uma tabela.¶

Perceba que o RSS converge rapidamente para um valor bem próximo à um limite ideal e, daí para frente, reduz muito pouco.¶

import plotly.figure_factory as ff
from numpy import *
import pandas as pd
import plotly.graph_objs as go

# y = mx + b
# m is slope, b is y-intercept
def compute_error_for_line_given_points(b, m, points):
    totalError = 0
    for i in range(0, len(points)):
        x = points.x[i]
        y = points.y[i]
        totalError += (y - (m * x + b)) ** 2
    return totalError / float(len(points))

def step_gradient(b_current, m_current, points, learningRate):
    b_gradient = 0
    m_gradient = 0
    N = float(len(points))
    for i in range(0, len(points)):
        x = points[i, 0]
        y = points[i, 1]
        b_gradient += -(2/N) * (y - ((m_current * x) + b_current))
        m_gradient += -(2/N) * x * (y - ((m_current * x) + b_current))
    new_b = b_current - (learningRate * b_gradient)
    new_m = m_current - (learningRate * m_gradient)
    return [new_b, new_m]

def gradient_descent_runner(points, starting_b, starting_m, learning_rate, num_iterations, plot=0):
    b = starting_b
    m = starting_m
    error = 0
    rsss = pd.DataFrame(dict(iteration=[],RSS=[]))
    for i in range(num_iterations):
        b, m = step_gradient(b, m, array(points), learning_rate)
        error = compute_error_for_line_given_points(b, m, points)
        #print("After {0} iterations b = {1}, m = {2}, error = {3}".format(i+1, b, m, error))
        rsss = rsss.append({'iteration': i+1,'RSS': error}, ignore_index=True)
    
    trace = go.Scatter(
        x = rsss.iteration,
        y = rsss.RSS,
        mode = "lines+markers",
        name = "decreasing error",
        marker = dict(color = 'rgba(80, 26, 80, 0.8)'),
        text= rsss.RSS)
    data = [trace]
    layout = dict(title = 'RSS per each iteration',yaxis= dict(title= 'RSS',ticklen= 5,zeroline= False),xaxis= dict(title= 'Iteration',ticklen= 5,zeroline= False))
    fig = dict(data = data, layout = layout)
    iplot(fig)
    
    return [b, m]

def run():
    points = pd.read_csv("income.csv")
    init_notebook_mode(connected=True)
    learning_rate = 0.0001
    initial_b = 0 # initial y-intercept guess
    initial_m = 0 # initial slope guess

    print("Starting gradient descent at b = {0}, m = {1}, error = {2}".format(initial_b, initial_m, compute_error_for_line_given_points(initial_b, initial_m, points)))
    print("Running...")

    run()

from plotly import version
from plotly.offline import download_plotlyjs, init_notebook_mode, plot, iplot

#import plotly.offline as py
import plotly.figure_factory as ff
from numpy import *
import pandas as pd
import plotly.graph_objs as go

# y = mx + b
# m is slope, b is y-intercept
def compute_error_for_line_given_points(b, m, points):
    totalError = 0
    for i in range(0, len(points)):
        x = points.x[i]
        y = points.y[i]
        totalError += (y - (m * x + b)) ** 2
    return totalError / float(len(points))

def step_gradient(b_current, m_current, points, learningRate):
    b_gradient = 0
    m_gradient = 0
    N = float(len(points))
    for i in range(0, len(points)):
        x = points[i, 0]
        y = points[i, 1]
        b_gradient += -(2/N) * (y - ((m_current * x) + b_current))
        m_gradient += -(2/N) * x * (y - ((m_current * x) + b_current))
    new_b = b_current - (learningRate * b_gradient)
    new_m = m_current - (learningRate * m_gradient)
    return [new_b, new_m]

def gradient_descent_runner(points, starting_b, starting_m, learning_rate, num_iterations, plot=0):
    b = starting_b
    m = starting_m
    error = 0
    rsss = pd.DataFrame(dict(iteration=[],RSS=[]))
    w0w1 = pd.DataFrame(dict(iteration=[],W0=[],W1=[]))
    for i in range(num_iterations):
        b, m = step_gradient(b, m, array(points), learning_rate)
        error = compute_error_for_line_given_points(b, m, points)
        #print("After {0} iterations b = {1}, m = {2}, error = {3}".format(i+1, b, m, error))
        rsss = rsss.append({'iteration': i+1,'RSS': error}, ignore_index=True)
        w0w1 = w0w1.append({'iteration': i+1,'W0': b,'W1': m}, ignore_index=True)
    

    # Creating trace1
    trace1 = go.Scatter(
        x = w0w1.W0,
        y = w0w1.iteration,
        mode = "lines",
        name = "W0",
        marker = dict(color = 'rgba(16, 112, 2, 0.8)'),
        text= w0w1.W0)
    # Creating trace2
    trace2 = go.Scatter(
        x = w0w1.W1,
        y = w0w1.iteration,
        mode = "lines",
        name = "W1",
        marker = dict(color = 'rgba(80, 26, 80, 0.8)'),
        text= w0w1.W1)
    data = [trace1, trace2]
    layout = dict(title = 'W0 and W1',xaxis= dict(title= 'W0',ticklen= 5,zeroline= False),yaxis= dict(title= 'W1',ticklen= 5,zeroline= False))
    fig = dict(data = data, layout = layout)
    iplot(fig)
    
    return [b, m]

def run():
    points = pd.read_csv("income.csv")
    init_notebook_mode(connected=True)
    learning_rate = 0.003
    initial_b = 0 # initial y-intercept guess
    initial_m = 0 # initial slope guess
    num_iterations = 16000
    print("Starting gradient descent at b = {0}, m = {1}, error = {2}".format(initial_b, initial_m, compute_error_for_line_given_points(initial_b, initial_m, points)))
    print("Running...")
    #print(points.info())
    [b, m] = gradient_descent_runner(points, initial_b, initial_m, learning_rate, num_iterations, 1)
    print("After {0} iterations b = {1}, m = {2}, error = {3}".format(num_iterations, b, m, compute_error_for_line_given_points(b, m, points)))

    
if __name__ == '__main__':
    run()

O total de iterações ainda é usado como critério de parada apenas para controle. Evitando assim eventuais loops infinitos durante os testes.¶

from plotly import version
from plotly.offline import download_plotlyjs, init_notebook_mode, plot, iplot

#import plotly.offline as py
import plotly.figure_factory as ff
from numpy import *
import pandas as pd
import plotly.graph_objs as go

# y = mx + b
# m is slope, b is y-intercept
def compute_error_for_line_given_points(b, m, points):
    totalError = 0
    for i in range(0, len(points)):
        x = points.x[i]
        y = points.y[i]
        totalError += (y - (m * x + b)) ** 2
    return totalError / float(len(points))

def step_gradient(b_current, m_current, points, learningRate, threshold):
    b_gradient = 0
    m_gradient = 0
    N = float(len(points))
    for i in range(0, len(points)):
        x = points[i, 0]
        y = points[i, 1]
        b_gradient += -(2/N) * (y - ((m_current * x) + b_current))
        m_gradient += -(2/N) * x * (y - ((m_current * x) + b_current))
    new_b = b_current - (learningRate * b_gradient)
    new_m = m_current - (learningRate * m_gradient)
    gradient = sqrt(b_gradient**2+m_gradient**2)
    return [new_b, new_m, gradient]
    
def gradient_descent_runner(points, starting_b, starting_m, learning_rate, num_iterations, threshold):
    b = starting_b
    m = starting_m
    gradient = 0
    error = 0
    gradients = pd.DataFrame(dict(iteration=[],gradient=[]))
    for i in range(num_iterations):
        b, m, gradient = step_gradient(b, m, array(points), learning_rate, threshold)
        if(gradient<threshold):
            break
        error = compute_error_for_line_given_points(b, m, points)
        #print("After {0} iterations b = {1}, m = {2}, error = {3}".format(i+1, b, m, error))
        gradients = gradients.append({'iteration': i+1,'gradient': gradient}, ignore_index=True)
    
    trace = go.Scatter(
        x = gradients.iteration,
        y = gradients.gradient,
        mode = "lines+markers",
        name = "descendent gradient",
        marker = dict(color = 'rgba(80, 26, 80, 0.8)'),
        text= gradients.gradient)
    data = [trace]
    layout = dict(title = 'Gradient per each iteration',yaxis= dict(title= 'gradient norm',ticklen= 5,zeroline= False),xaxis= dict(title= 'Iteration',ticklen= 5,zeroline= False))
    fig = dict(data = data, layout = layout)
    iplot(fig)
    
    return [b, m, gradient, i]

def run():
    points = pd.read_csv("income.csv")
    init_notebook_mode(connected=True)
    learning_rate = 0.0001
    initial_b = 0 # initial y-intercept guess
    initial_m = 0 # initial slope guess
    max_iterations = 1000
    threshold = 3.75
    print("Starting gradient descent at b = {0}, m = {1}, error = {2}".format(initial_b, initial_m, compute_error_for_line_given_points(initial_b, initial_m, points)))
    print("Running...")
    #print(points.info())
    [b, m, gradient, num_iterations] = gradient_descent_runner(points, initial_b, initial_m, learning_rate, max_iterations, threshold)
    print("After {0} iterations b = {1}, m = {2}, gradient norm = {3}, error = {4}".format(num_iterations+1, b, m, gradient, compute_error_for_line_given_points(b, m, points)))

    
if __name__ == '__main__':
    run()

7. Implemente a forma fechada (equações normais) de calcular os coeficientes de regressão (vide algoritmo nos slides). Compare o tempo de processamento com o gradiente descendente considerando sua solução do item 6.¶

Com base na solução do item 6, perceba em função da saída do código abaixo que, enquanto o método que percorre o gradiente descendente leva quase 49000 (quase um minuto) milessegundos para chegar ao resultado. Em contrapartida, o método baseado em encontrar as raízes das derivadas parciais do RSS leva apenas 8 milessegundos, tempo despresível em comparação com o anterior.¶

In [7]:
import plotly.figure_factory as ff
from numpy import *
import pandas as pd
import plotly.graph_objs as go
import time


def average_points(xs):
    average = 0
    total = len(xs)
    for i in range(0, total):
        average += xs[i]
    return average / total


def get_w1_from_points(points, w0, w1):
    average_x = average_points(points.x)
    average_y = average_points(points.y)
    w1_num = 0
    w1_denom = 0
    x = 0
    y = 0
    for i in range(0, len(points)):
        x = points.x[i]
        y = points.y[i]
        w1_num += (x - average_x)*(y - average_y)
        w1_denom += (x - average_x)**2
    w1 = w1_num / w1_denom
    w0 = average_y - w1*average_x
    return [w0, w1]

# y = mx + b
# m is slope, b is y-intercept
def compute_error_for_line_given_points(b, m, points):
    totalError = 0
    for i in range(0, len(points)):
        x = points.x[i]
        y = points.y[i]
        totalError += (y - (m * x + b)) ** 2
    return totalError / float(len(points))

def step_gradient(b_current, m_current, points, learningRate, threshold):
    b_gradient = 0
    m_gradient = 0
    N = float(len(points))
    for i in range(0, len(points)):
        x = points[i, 0]
        y = points[i, 1]
        b_gradient += -(2/N) * (y - ((m_current * x) + b_current))
        m_gradient += -(2/N) * x * (y - ((m_current * x) + b_current))
    new_b = b_current - (learningRate * b_gradient)
    new_m = m_current - (learningRate * m_gradient)
    gradient = sqrt(b_gradient**2+m_gradient**2)
    return [new_b, new_m, gradient]
    
def gradient_descent_runner(points, starting_b, starting_m, learning_rate, num_iterations, threshold):
    b = starting_b
    m = starting_m
    gradient = 0
    error = 0
    #gradients = pd.DataFrame(dict(iteration=[],gradient=[]))
    for i in range(num_iterations):
        b, m, gradient = step_gradient(b, m, array(points), learning_rate, threshold)
        if(gradient<threshold):
            break
        error = compute_error_for_line_given_points(b, m, points)
        #print("After {0} iterations b = {1}, m = {2}, error = {3}".format(i+1, b, m, error))
        #gradients = gradients.append({'iteration': i+1,'gradient': gradient}, ignore_index=True)
    
    return [b, m, gradient, i]

def run1(points):
    learning_rate = 0.003
    initial_b = 0 # initial y-intercept guess
    initial_m = 0 # initial slope guess
    max_iterations = 20000
    threshold = 0.03
    [b, m, gradient, num_iterations] = gradient_descent_runner(points, initial_b, initial_m, learning_rate, max_iterations, threshold)
    print("After {0} iterations b = {1}, m = {2}, error = {3}".format(num_iterations+1, b, m, compute_error_for_line_given_points(b, m, points)))

    

def run2(points):
    initial_b = 0 # initial y-intercept guess
    initial_m = 0 # initial slope guess
    [b, m] = get_w1_from_points(points, initial_b, initial_m)
    print("After {0} iterations b = {1}, m = {2}, error = {4}".format(1, b, m, gradient, compute_error_for_line_given_points(b, m, points)))


def run():
    points = pd.read_csv("income.csv")
    millis_1 = int(round(time.time() * 1000))
    run1(points)
    millis_2 = int(round(time.time() * 1000))
    run2(points)
    millis_3 = int(round(time.time() * 1000))
    print("Time elpased during gradient descendent method in milleseconds: {0}".format(millis_2-millis_1))
    print("Time elpased during fixed equation method in milleseconds: {0}".format(millis_3-millis_2))
    
    
if __name__ == '__main__':
    #%lprun -f run run()
    run()
